This student will investigate how dust devil activity changes throughout the Martian year at Jezero Crater. Using the full vortex catalog and associated solar longitude (Ls) values, they will analyze trends in detection frequency, vortex strength, and occurrence timing. They will create figures showing how dust devil activity varies with season and local time, identify periods of increased or decreased activity, and compare their results with previous observations from other Mars missions. Through this work, the student will gain experience in planetary climatology, statistical analysis, and scientific visualization while contributing to our understanding of seasonal atmospheric processes on Mars.
Seasonal Behavior of Dust Devils
Big Question
"When are dust devils most active during the Martian year?"
This works with the full catalog.

